title: Historical Tales, Vol VI: French
creator: Charles Morris
description: LibriVox recording of Historical Tales, Vol VI: French, by Charles Morris (1833-1922). Read by Kalynda. Volume VI of a series containing anecdotes and stories, some well-known, others less so, of particular countries. This fifth volume covers the history of France from the Hun invasion of Europe in the 5th century up to the Prussian War, describing history for children and young adults in an exciting and novel manner. (Introduction by Kalynda) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B Part 1 (115MB) Download M4B Part 2 (100MB)
